5ed2141d33f4"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "will be symmetric with respect to \[Phi], meaning it will have symmetry \
along the ",
 StyleBox["z",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "-axis. Therefore, the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubsuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["Y",
     FontSlant->"Italic"], "1", "0"], 
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{"\[Theta]", ",", "\[Phi]"}], ")"}]}]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.810112811439228*^9, 3.8101128248442793`*^9}, {
    3.810479494926491*^9, 3.8104795038498344`*^9}, {3.810479572543576*^9, 
    3.8104796147383184`*^9}, {3.8104802055659895`*^9, 
    3.8104802433915305`*^9}, {3.8104802785189395`*^9, 
    3.8104802814214115`*^9}, {3.810480477782269*^9, 3.8104805471507206`*^9}, {
    3.8104805927965565`*^9, 3.810480633017248*^9}, {3.8104807595294323`*^9, 
    3.8104809538100047`*^9}, {3.8104811300285854`*^9, 
    3.8104811403007636`*^9}, {3.8104812580010843`*^9, 
    3.8104813317580833`*^9}, {3.81048146789211*^9, 3.8104815557630205`*^9}, {
    3.8104817202872114`*^9, 3.8104817438715935`*^9}, 3.810481790764664*^9, 
    3.810481836241686*^9, {3.810481926951917*^9, 3.810481935802024*^9}, {
    3.8106609069078913`*^9, 3.81066090872985*^9}, {3.8106610360496655`*^9, 
    3.8106610794321012`*^9}, {3.8106611250786457`*^9, 
    3.8106611896874313`*^9}, {3.810718226403468*^9, 3.8107182918531866`*^9}, {
    3.8107241335231433`*^9, 3.81072417963937*^9}, {3.810725731557666*^9, 
    3.810725762073639*^9}, 3.810725827742792*^9, {3.810725864748572*^9, 
    3.810725881486649*^9}, 3.8107261709801435`*^9},ExpressionUUID->
  "f4e71531-52d6-48be-9ee4-abd1d3f9b7d8"],
 "corresponds to the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["p", "z"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c98e7795-c7c6-43df-ae68-a83f8fe2474b"],
 " atomic orbital. A visualization of the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["p", "z"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "50177d8f-ff69-4177-a90a-60ffc834fc36"],
 " orbital (and other atomic orbitals) for a fixed value of ",
 StyleBox["r",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " is shown in Figure 6.4. It is important to recognize that although these \
visualizations give the shape of the orbitals, they do not represent the \
probability of finding an electron at a given location because they do not \
take into account the radial dependence."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8107261762288046`*^9, 3.810726318022628*^9}, {
  3.810981777769161*^9, 3.810981826502711*^9}, {3.9171008507560086`*^9, 
