  3.8109859565496674`*^9}, {3.8109905631443915`*^9, 
  3.8109905778525996`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"f81745f1-22b4-465c-9cf9-\
8760257005e3"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "If we want to move to progressively more complex systems, the next obvious \
step would be the helium atom,",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["", "4"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "6d5bcaf2-49df-4ece-8d21-e45319af76b8"],
 "He, which comprises two electrons and a nucleus containing two protons and \
two neutrons. Treating the nucleus as a particle of mass ",
 StyleBox["M",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", we can write out the time-independent Schr\[ODoubleDot]dinger equation \
for the helium atom as"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.81099063376393*^9, 3.8109907597592735`*^9}, {
  3.81099126391743*^9, 3.810991293941801*^9}, {3.810991430569471*^9, 
  3.8109914938857627`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"3cafaf09-7c82-47e0-b9a1-\
cdf0dab38af2"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"(", 
